{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Standard ERC20 repayments are impossible because the pool uses `transferFrom(address(this), ...)` when forwarding funds","locations":["0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1850","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1858"],"claim":"`repay()` first pulls tokens from the payer into the pool, then tries to forward those tokens with `IERC20(_supportedCurrency).transferFrom(address(this), _fundSource, ...)` and `transferFrom(address(this), _controlPlane, ...)`. For standard ERC20s, `transferFrom` spends an allowance granted by `address(this)`, but the pool never approves itself, so the outbound transfers revert.","impact":"Normal repayment cannot complete, so borrowers cannot recover collateral through the intended path and lender principal cannot be repaid through `repay()`. Live positions are forced into bad debt or privileged intervention paths.","paths":["A borrower calls `repay(nftID, repayAmount, pineWallet)` on an active loan.","The inbound `transferFrom(msg.sender, address(this), repayAmount)` succeeds.","The first outbound `transferFrom(address(this), _fundSource, ...)` or the fee transfer to `_controlPlane` reverts because the pool has no self-allowance."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Repayments between lender-rate and client-rate outstanding can clear the loan without returning collateral","locations":["0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1778","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1779","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1793","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1825","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1867","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1869"],"claim":"`repay()` decides whether a payment is full using `outstanding()` on a temporary copy whose interest rate is first replaced with the higher client rate. After processing a partial repayment, it resets that temporary copy back to the lower lender rate and then clears the loan if `repayAmount >= outstanding(termsWithRealRate)`. Once protocol spread has accrued, a payment that is too small for the client-rate debt can still satisfy the final lender-rate comparison.","impact":"A borrower can pay less than the actual debt, have the loan record erased without receiving the NFT back, leave `_fundSource` underpaid by the unpaid spread amount, and permanently strand the collateral inside the pool while `_currentLoanAmount` also remains overstated.","paths":["Interest accrues so client-rate outstanding exceeds lender-rate outstanding.","The borrower repays an amount that is below client-rate outstanding but at least the lender-rate outstanding.","The function takes the partial-repayment branch, so no NFT is transferred back.","The final lender-rate comparison at `clearLoanTerms()` still passes, zeroing the loan while the collateral remains trapped in the contract."],"round":1,"source_agents":["merge_review"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"PineWallet-backed loans cannot be liquidated consistently","locations":["0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1688","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1699","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1748","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1774","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1818","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1907","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1914","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1925"],"claim":"When `pineWallet != address(0)`, the pool escrows `pineMirrorID` from the clone collection, but the loan is still keyed by the underlying `nftID`. `withdrawERC721()` only clears `_loans[nftID]` when `collection == _supportedCollection`; otherwise it just transfers the caller-supplied token. As a result, liquidating the actual escrowed mirror token moves collateral out without clearing the debt, while attempting liquidation with the underlying collection reverts because the pool never held that token.","impact":"Defaulted PineWallet positions can become unliquidatable or end up with collateral removed while the debt stays active, creating permanent lockups, zombie debt, and leaked borrowing-capacity accounting.","paths":["A borrower opens a loan with a nonzero `pineWallet`, so the pool receives `pineMirrorID` instead of the underlying NFT.","The control plane attempts liquidation after default.","If it calls `withdrawERC721(pineWallet, pineMirrorID, target, true)`, the mirror token leaves the pool but `_loans[nftID]` is not cleared.","If it instead calls `withdrawERC721(_supportedCollection, nftID, target, true)`, the transfer reverts because the pool does not own the underlying NFT."],"round":1,"source_agents":["merge_review"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Liquidations permanently consume the global loan cap because `_currentLoanAmount` is never reduced","locations":["0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1590","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1721","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1802","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1839","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1914","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1923"],"claim":"`_currentLoanAmount` is incremented on every borrow and only reduced during repayment. The liquidation path in `withdrawERC721(..., true)` clears the loan terms directly and never subtracts the liquidated principal from `_currentLoanAmount`.","impact":"After enough defaults or liquidations, `_currentLoanAmount` can remain near `_maxLoanLimit` even though those positions are already closed, eventually blocking all new borrowing and causing a protocol-level denial of service.","paths":["Loans are opened until `_currentLoanAmount` approaches `_maxLoanLimit`.","Those loans are closed through `withdrawERC721(..., true)` instead of repayment.","Because liquidation does not release principal from `_currentLoanAmount`, later `borrow()` calls fail the total-loan-limit check."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Collateral can be liquidated without any on-chain unhealthy-loan check","locations":["0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1907","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1913","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1914","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1923"],"claim":"`withdrawERC721()` treats `msg.sender == _controlPlane` plus `liquidation == true` as sufficient to emit a liquidation event and erase loan state. The pool never verifies that the loan is expired or otherwise unhealthy before seizing supported collateral.","impact":"Any bug, compromise, or over-permissive code path in `_controlPlane` can seize healthy borrower collateral immediately and write off the corresponding debt inside the pool.","paths":["A borrower opens a healthy loan through `borrow()`.","Before expiry, `_controlPlane` calls `withdrawERC721(_supportedCollection, nftID, attacker, true)`.","The pool clears `_loans[nftID]` and transfers the collateral to `attacker` without checking loan health."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Uninitialized pool deployments can be taken over through the public initializer","locations":["0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1535","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1543"],"claim":"The pool exposes a public `initialize()` entry point but does not disable initializers in a constructor. Any deployment or clone that is created without atomic initialization remains claimable by the first external caller, who then becomes owner via `__Ownable_init()`.","impact":"If a pool instance is ever deployed and initialized in separate steps, an attacker can seize ownership and later pause the pool or withdraw assets that reach that instance.","paths":["A new pool instance is deployed but not initialized in the same transaction.","An attacker calls `initialize(...)` first and becomes owner.","The attacker uses owner-only functions such as `pause()`, `withdraw()`, `withdrawERC20()`, or `withdrawERC1155()`."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Anyone can take zero-fee flash loans from any token allowance granted by `_fundSource`","locations":["0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1607","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1614","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1625","0x2405913d54fc46eeaf3fb092bfb099f46803872f/Contract.sol:1635"],"claim":"`flashLoan()` is permissionless, `amountFee` is hardcoded to zero, and the caller can choose any `_reserve`. For ERC20 reserves, the pool sources liquidity directly from `_fundSource` with `transferFrom`, so every token allowance that `_fundSource` has granted this pool becomes publicly available for intra-transaction borrowing.","impact":"Attackers can freely mobilize lender-approved assets for governance attacks, oracle manipulation, or other external strategies without paying the lender and without being limited to `_supportedCurrency`.","paths":["`_fundSource` has approved token `T` to this pool.","An attacker calls `flashLoan(attackerReceiver, T, amount, data)`.","The pool transfers `T` from `_fundSource` to the attacker-controlled receiver and only requires same-transaction principal restoration."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Flash loan returns funds without verification, enabling fund theft","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Incorrect. The post-loan check at `1607-1650` requires `_fundSource` or the pool to end with exactly the same balance as before when `amountFee == 0`, so the borrower cannot keep the funds."},{"title":"Block-based loan limit can be bypassed within same block","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Incorrect. `updateBlockLoanAmount()` adds the new amount first and immediately reverts if the cumulative amount for the current block reaches or exceeds `blockLoanLimit`, so bundling transactions does not bypass the cap."},{"title":"Signature can be replayed across different loans with same parameters","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Not independently reportable here. A single NFT cannot hold concurrent loans, and reusing the same valuation for the same NFT before expiry is largely the intended behavior of this verifier."},{"title":"Repay can result in underflow when repayAmount less than outstanding","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The claimed arithmetic-underflow path is not the real issue. The actual repayment failure is the outbound `transferFrom(address(this), ...)` bug captured separately."},{"title":"Missing check for loan existence before liquidation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The specific claim about liquidating already repaid NFTs is incorrect because full repayment transfers the NFT out before loan terms are cleared. The broader liquidation-trust issue is already captured separately."},{"title":"No validation that _controlPlane is a valid contract","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is owner/configuration hygiene rather than an intrinsic exploit path in the pool."},{"title":"Precision loss in fee calculations","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is ordinary integer truncation with negligible impact and is not reportable."},{"title":"PineWallet clone validation only checks factory whitelist","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Insufficient support from the available code. The pool also requires ownership of the derived mirror token, and any exploit would depend on external factory or wallet behavior not shown here."},{"title":"Valuation signatures are replayable across pools and borrowing contexts","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Too speculative as a standalone issue. The signature appears to authorize valuation data only, while amount and duration are intentionally bounded by pool parameters; concrete cross-pool harm would require extra deployment or signer-reuse assumptions."}]}
